wooden sign~
After brushing some snow of the sign, you notice that a plaque
has been fastened to it.  Examining the plaque, you read the
following message:

   "Hail travellers! Know that ye have entered the realm of
Jotunheim, home of the fearsome frost giants.  The giants do not
look kindy upon strangers, so ye should be wary at all times.
North of here, in the foothills of the Vinsaar mountains, there
be a ferry across the Iving river.  The ferry leads to Asgaard, a
much more hospitable place than this.  South lies the Gindra
mountains, although ye would be wise to avoid traveling in the
monster infested mountains of Jotunheim.  The Torvald river rises
in the in the east in the mountains behind the city of Utgard.
River travel is unlikely; the river is usually frozen over.  This
land is not known for its balmy weather, so I'd advise that ye
carry some form of protection against the cold, be it warm
clothing or some sort of magical protection."

                                                 Silverwing
